moab-balance
============

This project includes work derived from microsoft/moabian
(https://github.com/microsoft/moabian), which is licensed under the
MIT License, Copyright (c) Microsoft Corporation.

Specifically, the following pieces are derived from that project:

  * The SPI command set, opcodes and 8-byte packet layout used by
    `moab_balance/hat.py` to talk to the Moab HAT firmware.
  * The plate-angles-to-servo-positions inverse kinematics formula in
    `moab_balance/kinematics.py` (function originally named
    `plate_angles_to_servo_positions` in `sw/hardware.py`).
  * Camera capture parameters (frame size 384x288 cropped to 256x256,
    plate diameter 0.225 m, field of view ratio 1.05, camera mounted at
    +30 degrees relative to the plate axes) in `moab_balance/camera.py`
    and `moab_balance/vision.py`.
  * The HAT MCU bootloader GPIO sequence and `mcumgr` invocation in
    `firmware/flash-hat.sh` (derived from `bin/flash`).

In addition, this project redistributes the following binary file verbatim
from microsoft/moabian:

  * `firmware/v3.bin` — Build 3.0 (May 2021) of the Project Moab HAT firmware
    (a Zephyr / MCUboot binary, 112 064 bytes,
    SHA-256 a2ad9c0c2585c3509b2b7f05c581ef16f3a5e031200096f56b88d303b870779e).
    Originally at `fw/v3.bin` in microsoft/moabian. Source for the firmware
    lives at `microsoft/moabian/fw/src/`.

The pre-built SD image build pipeline (`image/`) cross-compiles
[`mcumgr`](https://github.com/apache/mynewt-mcumgr-cli) (the Apache MyNewt
Simple Management Protocol CLI) from source and bundles the resulting binary
at `/usr/local/bin/mcumgr` in the produced image. `mcumgr` is licensed under
the Apache License 2.0; only the binary is redistributed, not the source.

